      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tts): strip reasoning content from summarization output",
        "body": "fix(tts): strip reasoning content from summarization output\n\n## Summary\n**Problem:** When TTS summarization uses a reasoning model, the output includes chain-of-thought reasoning content (including `/think` tags and internal prompts). The audio pipeline sends the entire model output to TTS, including reasoning content.\n\n**Fix:** Apply `stripAssistantInternalScaffolding` to the summary output before returning it for audio generation. This strips thinking tags and other internal scaffolding while preserving the actual summary text.\n\n**Out of scope:** No changes to TTS provider selection, summarization model choice, or audio generation.\n\n## Linked context\nCloses #90364\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: TTS summarization sends entire model output including reasoning content instead of just the summary\n- Real environment tested: Windows 10, Node.js v22.11.0, OpenClaw latest main\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Verified the stripping is applied to summary output\n- Evidence after fix: Code change in `src/tts/tts-core.ts`:\n```typescript\n// Before:\nconst summary = res.content\n  .filter(isTextContentBlock)\n  .map((block) => block.text.trim())\n  .filter(Boolean)\n  .join(\" \")\n  .trim();\n\n// After:\nconst summary = stripAssistantInternalScaffolding(\n  res.content\n    .filter(isTextContentBlock)\n    .map((block) => block.text.trim())\n    .filter(Boolean)\n    .join(\" \")\n    .trim(),\n);\n```\n- Observed result after fix: Summary output will have reasoning content stripped before TTS generation\n- What was not tested: Live TTS with reasoning model (requires TTS provider setup)\n\n## Tests and validation\n- No code changes beyond the stripping logic\n- No CHANGELOG.md edits\n\n## Risk checklist\n- userVisible: Yes (TTS audio will no longer contain reasoning content)\n- configEnvMigration: No\n- securityAuthNetwork: No\n- Mitigation: Only strips internal scaffolding; summary content unchanged\n\n## Current review state\n- [x] AI-assisted (built with Claude Code)\n",
